main event: A round object the size of a dinner plate was observed at an altitude of 3,000-4,000 feet, changing color from bright red to bright white to blue-green over 12 minutes.
interesting points: The object descended from around 3,000-4,000 feet altitude.
A sound was attributed to the object by the observer.
The object was possibly an unauthorized helicopter, a dirigible, or an experimental device.
A radar operator observed a quite bright red object the size of a baseball, traveling at a high rate of speed and hovering before disappearing in a flash.
sighted object: round object the size of a dinner plate
photographs: yes, the report indicates a 4x5 inch photograph was included, but no photograph was provided in the image
